title: Plane Lands in Mississippi After Pilot Threatened to Crash Into a Walmart; Governor had called it a dangerous situation; no injuries reported
text:
"The plane over North MS is down," Gov. Reeves tweeted. "Thankful the situation has been resolved and that no one was injured."

The governor didn't identify the pilot. Tupelo police also didn't identify the pilot.

At about 5 a.m. Central Time on Saturday, a person claiming to be the pilot called 911 and threatened to crash into a Walmart in Tupelo, police said. Police evacuated the store and officers were communicating with the pilot, police said.
